---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="AI Governance for Teams | Tenure"
  description="Nobody asks who owns the Anthropic keys until someone leaves. Tenure gives every engineer their own PAT, a central proxy, SCIM deprovisioning, and a full audit trail. Access governance for AI that actually works."
  canonical="https://tenureai.dev/teams/ai-governance"
>

<style>
.gov-hero {
  padding: 6rem 2rem 5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.gov-breadcrumb {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.5rem;
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}
.gov-breadcrumb a { color: var(--muted); transition: color 0.15s; }
.gov-breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--text); }
.gov-breadcrumb-sep { color: var(--border2); }

.gov-eyebrow {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--accent);
  margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  display: block;
}

.gov-hero h1 {
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.25rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.1;
  letter-spacing: -0.03em;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
}

.gov-hero h1 .accent { color: var(--accent); }

.gov-hero-sub {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
}

.gov-ctas {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.btn-primary {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  background: var(--accent);
  color: #fff;
  padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem;
  border-radius: 8px;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  transition: background 0.15s;
  text-decoration: none;
}
.btn-primary:hover { background: var(--accent2); }

.btn-secondary {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  background: transparent;
  color: var(--text);
  border: 1px solid var(--border2);
  padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem;
  border-radius: 8px;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  font-weight: 500;
  transition: border-color 0.15s;
  text-decoration: none;
}
.btn-secondary:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }

/* ── QUIET PROBLEM SECTION ── */
.quiet-section {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.section-label {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--accent);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  display: block;
}

.quiet-section h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.quiet-section p {
  color: var(--muted);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin: 0 0 1rem;
}

.scenario-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 1px;
  margin-top: 3.5rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
  background: var(--border);
}

@media (max-width: 680px) { .scenario-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

.scenario-card {
  background: var(--surface);
  padding: 1.75rem;
  position: relative;
}

.scenario-card::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  height: 2px;
  background: transparent;
  transition: background 0.2s;
}

.scenario-card:hover::before {
  background: var(--red);
}

.scenario-who {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  color: var(--dim);
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
}

.scenario-card h3 {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
  line-height: 1.35;
}

.scenario-card p {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin: 0;
}

.scenario-card code {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.78em;
  background: rgba(196, 83, 83, 0.1);
  color: var(--red);
  padding: 0.1em 0.3em;
  border-radius: 3px;
}

/* ── PROBLEM LIST (the blunt inventory) ── */
.problem-section {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  background: var(--surface);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.problem-section h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 1.9rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0 0 3rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.problem-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.problem-item {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 2.5rem 1fr;
  gap: 1rem;
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  align-items: start;
  background: var(--bg);
  transition: background 0.15s;
}
.problem-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.problem-item:hover { background: rgba(196,83,83,0.03); }

.problem-num {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  color: var(--red);
  opacity: 0.6;
  padding-top: 0.15rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.problem-text {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.problem-text strong {
  color: var(--text);
  font-weight: 600;
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  font-size: 0.92rem;
}

.question-section {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.question-block {
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 2.5rem;
  margin-top: 2rem;
}

.question-line {
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 1rem;
  padding: 0.9rem 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.question-line:last-child { border-bottom: none; padding-bottom: 0; }
.question-line:first-child { padding-top: 0; }

.question-q {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  flex: 1;
  line-height: 1.5;
}

.question-a {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  color: var(--red);
  white-space: nowrap;
  opacity: 0.85;
}

.question-a.ok {
  color: var(--accent);
}

.solution-section {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.solution-section h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 1.9rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.solution-section > .container > p {
  color: var(--muted);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin: 0 0 3rem;
}

.solution-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 1.25rem;
}

@media (max-width: 680px) { .solution-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

.solution-card {
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 1.75rem;
  position: relative;
  overflow: hidden;
  transition: border-color 0.2s;
}

.solution-card:hover {
  border-color: rgba(0,168,173,0.3);
}

.solution-card-accent {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
  height: 2px;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent), transparent);
}

.solution-card h3 {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0.75rem 0 0.5rem;
}

.solution-card p {
  font-size: 0.83rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.65;
  margin: 0 0 1rem;
}

.solution-pill {
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  color: var(--accent);
  background: rgba(0,168,173,0.08);
  border: 1px solid rgba(0,168,173,0.15);
  padding: 0.25em 0.6em;
  border-radius: 4px;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
}

.solution-icon {
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  display: block;
}

.audit-section {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  background: var(--surface);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.audit-section h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 1.9rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.audit-section > .container > p {
  color: var(--muted);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin: 0 0 3rem;
}

.audit-log {
  background: var(--bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.audit-log-header {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr 110px 90px;
  gap: 1rem;
  padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  background: var(--surface2);
}

.audit-log-header span {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.65rem;
  color: var(--dim);
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

.audit-log-row {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr 110px 90px;
  gap: 1rem;
  padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  align-items: center;
  transition: background 0.1s;
}
.audit-log-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.audit-log-row:hover { background: var(--surface2); }

.audit-ts {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  color: var(--dim);
}

.audit-user {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  color: var(--text);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.5rem;
}

.audit-user-dot {
  width: 6px;
  height: 6px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background: var(--accent);
  opacity: 0.6;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.audit-user-dot.revoked {
  background: var(--red);
}

.audit-action {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  color: var(--muted);
}

.audit-status {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: flex-end;
}

.audit-badge {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.65rem;
  padding: 0.2em 0.5em;
  border-radius: 4px;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
}

.audit-badge.ok {
  background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1);
  color: var(--green);
  border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
}

.audit-badge.revoked {
  background: rgba(196, 83, 83, 0.1);
  color: var(--red);
  border: 1px solid rgba(196, 83, 83, 0.2);
}

.audit-badge.active {
  background: rgba(0,168,173,0.08);
  color: var(--accent);
  border: 1px solid rgba(0,168,173,0.2);
}

@media (max-width: 680px) {
  .audit-log-header { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  .audit-log-header span:nth-child(3),
  .audit-log-header span:nth-child(4) { display: none; }
  .audit-log-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
  .audit-log-row > .audit-action,
  .audit-log-row > .audit-status { display: none; }
}

.offboard-section {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.offboard-section h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 1.9rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.offboard-section > .container > p {
  color: var(--muted);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin: 0 0 3rem;
}

.offboard-flow {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0;
}

.offboard-step {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr;
  gap: 1.25rem;
  align-items: start;
  position: relative;
}

.offboard-step-track {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0;
}

.offboard-node {
  width: 28px;
  height: 28px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
}

.offboard-node.trigger {
  background: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1);
  border: 1px solid rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.3);
  color: var(--amber);
}

.offboard-node.auto {
  background: rgba(0,168,173,0.08);
  border: 1px solid rgba(0,168,173,0.2);
  color: var(--accent);
}

.offboard-connector {
  width: 1px;
  height: 2rem;
  background: var(--border2);
  margin: 0.25rem 0;
}

.offboard-content {
  padding-bottom: 2rem;
}

.offboard-content h4 {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0.3rem 0 0.3rem;
  line-height: 1.3;
}

.offboard-content p {
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.6;
  margin: 0;
}

.offboard-tag {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.62rem;
  color: var(--amber);
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  display: block;
}

.offboard-tag.auto { color: var(--accent); }

.last-used-section {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  background: var(--surface);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}

.last-used-section h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 3vw, 1.9rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.last-used-section > .container > p {
  color: var(--muted);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin: 0 0 3rem;
}

.pat-table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 12px;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.pat-table th {
  padding: 0.65rem 1.1rem;
  text-align: left;
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.65rem;
  color: var(--dim);
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  background: var(--surface2);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  font-weight: 500;
}

.pat-table td {
  padding: 0.85rem 1.1rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  font-size: 0.83rem;
  vertical-align: middle;
}

.pat-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
.pat-table tr:hover td { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }

.pat-name {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: var(--text);
}

.pat-owner { color: var(--muted); }

.pat-last {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  color: var(--muted);
}

.pat-last.stale { color: var(--amber); }
.pat-last.fresh { color: var(--green); }
.pat-last.never { color: var(--red); opacity: 0.7; }

.pat-scope {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  color: var(--dim);
}

.gov-cta-section {
  padding: 6rem 2rem;
}

.gov-cta-inner {
  text-align: center;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.gov-cta-inner h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  color: var(--text);
  margin: 0 0 1rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.gov-cta-inner p {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin: 0 0 2rem;
}

.gov-cta-btns {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  justify-content: center;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}
</style>

<section class="gov-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="gov-breadcrumb">
      <a href="/teams">Teams</a>
      <span class="gov-breadcrumb-sep">›</span>
      <span>AI Governance</span>
    </div>
    <span class="gov-eyebrow">AI Governance</span>
    <h1>Who owns the <span class="accent">API key</span>?</h1>
    <p class="gov-hero-sub">
      Everyone on the team is using AI. Nobody is sure which credentials they're using, whose name the account is under, or what happens when someone leaves. This is the governance problem teams don't talk about until it becomes urgent.
    </p>
    <div class="gov-ctas">
      <a href="/docs/teams/governance" class="btn-primary">Read the deployment guide →</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/tenurehq/tenure" class="btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="quiet-section">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-label">The situation</span>
    <h2>AI access at most companies is an accident waiting to happen.</h2>
    <p>
      It starts with one person creating an API key. Then a second person needs access, so they get the key too. Then a contractor needs it. Then someone pastes it into a shared <code>.env</code> file in the repo. Then that person leaves.
    </p>
    <p>
      At no point did anyone say this was fine. It just happened, incrementally, because there was no structured alternative.
    </p>

    <div class="scenario-grid">
      <div class="scenario-card">
        <div class="scenario-who">The engineer</div>
        <h3>The key is in the <code>.env.local</code>. Everyone has a copy.</h3>
        <p>It was the path of least resistance. Now it's in six engineers' home directories, maybe a few editor config files, probably the CI logs from that one incident in March.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scenario-card">
        <div class="scenario-who">The contractor</div>
        <h3>They finished the project four months ago. The key still works.</h3>
        <p>Nobody thought to revoke it. There's no list of who has which keys. The contractor probably still has access and either doesn't know it or doesn't care.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scenario-card">
        <div class="scenario-who">The security team</div>
        <h3>Someone asks: can you show me who has access to the AI APIs?</h3>
        <p>The honest answer is no. There's a billing dashboard that shows usage, but nothing that maps requests to identities, and no way to know which keys are still live.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="scenario-card">
        <div class="scenario-who">The offboarding checklist</div>
        <h3>There's no line item for AI credentials.</h3>
        <p>The IT runbook covers email, GitHub, Slack, AWS. It has not been updated for the reality that engineers now have personal access to a dozen AI provider accounts.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="question-section">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-label">The question you can't answer</span>
    <h2>What happens when someone asks you to prove control?</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--muted); font-size:0.95rem; max-width:580px; line-height:1.75; margin:0 0 0.5rem;">
      Not "what do you think is probably true." Prove it. With a timestamp and a name.
    </p>

    <div class="question-block">
      <div class="question-line">
        <span class="question-q">Which engineers currently have access to your Anthropic API?</span>
        <span class="question-a">unknown</span>
      </div>
      <div class="question-line">
        <span class="question-q">When did the contractor who left in February last make a request?</span>
        <span class="question-a">no record</span>
      </div>
      <div class="question-line">
        <span class="question-q">Who made the 4am request that spiked your bill last month?</span>
        <span class="question-a">no record</span>
      </div>
      <div class="question-line">
        <span class="question-q">How many active tokens exist right now?</span>
        <span class="question-a">unknown</span>
      </div>
      <div class="question-line">
        <span class="question-q">Can you revoke a single engineer's access in under a minute?</span>
        <span class="question-a">no</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="solution-section">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-label">How Tenure solves it</span>
    <h2>One key at the proxy. One token per person.</h2>
    <p>
      Tenure sits between your engineers and the AI provider. Your org's real API key lives in one place. Every engineer authenticates through their own personal access token. Access is per-identity from the start.
    </p>

    <div class="solution-grid">
      <div class="solution-card">
        <div class="solution-card-accent"></div>
        <span class="solution-icon">🔑</span>
        <h3>Personal access tokens</h3>
        <p>Every engineer gets their own PAT. Their token is theirs. Their requests are attributed to them. Revoking one person's access doesn't require rotating a shared key or touching anyone else's setup.</p>
        <span class="solution-pill">PAT per user</span>
      </div>

      <div class="solution-card">
        <div class="solution-card-accent"></div>
        <span class="solution-icon">🌐</span>
        <h3>Central proxy</h3>
        <p>The actual provider API key lives in one place: the Tenure deployment inside your cluster. Engineers never see it. It never lives in a <code>.env</code> file. It never leaves your infrastructure.</p>
        <span class="solution-pill">Zero credential scatter</span>
      </div>

      <div class="solution-card">
        <div class="solution-card-accent"></div>
        <span class="solution-icon">⚡</span>
        <h3>SCIM deprovisioning</h3>
        <p>Tenure integrates with your identity provider via SCIM. When you deprovision an engineer in Okta, Azure AD, or Google Workspace, their Tenure access is revoked automatically. No manual step. No gap.</p>
        <span class="solution-pill">Automatic offboarding</span>
      </div>

      <div class="solution-card">
